        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 16 at 6:28PM CDT until May 16 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hardy, or 10
miles southeast of Mammoth Spring, moving east at 65 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Armstrong...                      Dalton...
Brakebill...                      Warm Springs...
Elm Store...                      Wirth...
Saddler Falls...                  Hardy...
Cherokee Village...
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for eastern and
north central Arkansas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
